do one's block
Homonym Number:
Word Class:phrase
Sense Number:
Definition:to become angry, excited, upset
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:cf. do one's bun/loaf/scone; lose one's block
